programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: The team are responding to reports of a life-or death emergency; Jim Te Whata has been pulled from the water cold, unconscious and not breathing.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team battles to save a man trapped in his overturned Land Rover on Rakino Island; a star rugby player at Onewhero may have broken his neck after a scrum collapsed, and a man out cycling on Waiheke is clinging to life after a cardiac arrest.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 04
programme.desc: Fog, rain and snow means that a visit to the Eifel region is not that pleasant right now. Nevertheless, the hardcore drivers are out of the track and are not letting the weather get in their way.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 05
programme.desc: The Nürburgring. Here you can really let your hair down on a spectacular and difficult race track and learn how to get fit for motor sports. That is why motor fans come here to the Nürburgring throughout the year!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 06
programme.desc: On today's episode, we will be treating you to some very entertaining clips from the Nürburgring. Expect to see the pedal on the metal and rubber burning up the place!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 07
programme.desc: The weather has cleared up a bit on the Nürburgring and we are finally back on the track. As soon as the snow and ice has gone the horsepower junkies return to the ring to tear it up once again.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 08
programme.desc: On today's show we will be showing you the history of a racing legend who has won the 24-hour race four times in a row: Olaf Manthey. Stick around and perhaps you will find out the secret of his success.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 09
programme.desc: Christian Menzel has asked presenter Miriam to participate in some driver safety training! He will be showing you tips and tricks on what to do in emergency situations.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 10
programme.desc: Spring has finally melted away the snow on the track and life on the Nürburgring is starting to flourish once again. It is full of drivers with gasoline in their hearts and cars that roar around the ring.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 11
programme.desc: It is time once again for the VLN Endurance Racing Championship! While the drivers are already out there doing test laps, we will be taking you behind the scenes and showing what really goes on in the pit lanes.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 12
programme.desc: Great cars and pretty girls. The Nürburgring is shaking as the VLN begins its second leg of the tournament. We will be commentating on this exciting competition, as well as showing highlights of the BMW's 1st leg win.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 13
programme.desc: The fourth race of the VLN season is regarded as a dress rehearsal for the 24 hour race. For the top teams and best drivers this is the last opportunity for a real hard test.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.

programme.title: Track Masters
programme.desc: Some heavy guns are going to be driven around the ring on today's show. We are at the Truck Grand Prix and shall be following the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he gets ready for qualifying.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 16
programme.desc: On today's show, we will be taking a look at the RCN Challenge - the BMW Driving Experience. Also on the show, we will be paying a visit to the Devils Diner - the indoor meeting place for drivers on the ring!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Weapon of Choice

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: River of Blood
programme.desc: Two hunters discover a blood-drenched car, its owner riddled with buckshot. Lt. Joe Kenda learns the car was reported stolen the day before, he follows its trail to a group of unlikely suspects.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Poker Face
programme.desc: A group of friends discover the corpse of entrepreneur Jamie Foster hidden under a blanket. Kenda e discovers that Foster’s business put him in close quarters with a host of unsavory characters.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Raise the Dead

programme.title: Paranormal State: Good Vs. Evil
programme.desc: PRS visits a western Pennsylvania couple wracked by a torrent of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Family Ties
programme.desc: Jimmie is haunted by the apparition of a mysterious old woman who peers at him in the bathroom of his family's Petersburg, VA home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Room & Board
programme.desc: The owners of a vacation lodge in the remote town of North Hudson, NY, feel their woodsy getaway is plagued by negative spirits.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lady Vampire
programme.desc: PRS investigates a case involving single mom, Dawn, and her 5-year-old daughter, both of whom are tormented by the appearance of a hag they call "lady vampire."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II
programme.desc: PRS returns to the site of one of their most famous cases, Daisytown, PA, where they had discovered a glove print of an old miner that they determined was the spirit of a Great-Grandfather.
programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Homecoming
programme.desc: Ryan brings PRS to his hometown of Sumter, SC to investigate a chilling case where a young boy was tragically shot and killed on a front doorstep while trick-or-treating on Halloween.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Mothman
programme.desc: Ryan takes his team to Point Pleasant, West Virginia to investigate his own personal holy grail of paranormal lore: the mysterious Mothman.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dwelling of the Dead
programme.desc: A single mom claims she is being physically assaulted by a spirit in her Kentucky home. Ryan first explores a natural explanation for the alleged phenomena. But the client's five-year-old son also sees spirits, and his sightings appear to line up.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder
programme.desc: A large family in Shrewsbury, MA, has been living with a spirit for the last 40 years. To most of the siblings, the entity is menacing and evil, but Sandy seems to have a different connection.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Devil in Syracuse
programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Owlpen Manor
programme.desc: Owlpen Manor is allegedly home to several ghosts. Queen Margaret of Anjou, wife to Henry VI, an alchemist and a young girl are all said to roam the 16th-century manor. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Craig-Y-Nos
programme.desc: This derelict castle in the heart of Wales has been home to a famous opera singer and a World War II hospital. This beautiful building is so haunted that the team has to spend the night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Jamaica Inn
programme.desc: This famous old coaching inn has stood in the middle of Bodmin Moor for hundreds of years. The team investigates possible poltergeist activity in a room that no staff member will enter alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Croxteth Hall
programme.desc: A manor in Liverpool awaits the team in a place that time forgot. A boy standing beside the fireplace in the dining room and a horrifying hooded man are among several ghosts reported here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hellfire Caves
programme.desc: The team encounters ghostly lights and voices in the Hellfire Caves. These legendary tunnels were once home to the notorious Hellfire Club, practitioners of satanic rituals, murder and debauchery.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Manor House
programme.desc: The team investigate the Manor House in Ferryhill, County Durham. Now a hotel, this historic house has had many uses over the centuries and is said to house several ghosts.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Mary King's Close
programme.desc: The team visits Edinburgh's Old Town to investigate Mary King's Close, one of the many narrow alleyways off the Royal Mile. Unlike most, this one is long shrouded in tales of ghosts and murders.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Wellington Hotel
programme.desc: The team visits the Wellington Hotel, an old coaching inn that has many mysteries surrounding suspicious deaths. The ghost of Thomas Hardy and his wife are said to haunt the upper floors.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Dust Child
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark must help an Amerasian girl facing racial prejudice when she goes to live with her father's family in the United States.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Hotel Of Dreams
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are bellhops at a hotel that has been given to an aimless young man by his father. They must deal with an unkind boss, an obnoxious kid and a difficult guest.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Song For Christmas
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help a heartless used car salesman reconsider his actions on Christmas Eve.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Plane Death
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark investigate a gang of drug smugglers after an old friend of Mark's has mysteriously disappeared.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: One Winged Angels
programme.desc: Jonathan attempts to fan the flames of love between a woman and her ex-husband's best friend. But his efforts backfire when he falls for the woman himself.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Going Home, Going Home
programme.desc: Mark is in a state between life and death when he's critically injured in a car accident. Jonathan takes Mark back to childhood to give him a second chance to tell his grandfather how much he loves him.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: As Difficult as ABC
programme.desc: Jonathan steps in when a heart condition sidelines a promising basketball player's dreams.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Child of God
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are on hand when a dying woman attempts a reconciliation with her estranged father. She is a single mother who wants her family to take the child.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Fashion 911
programme.desc: Between two failed marriages, the loss of her father and caring for her ailing mother, Zoe feels life taking its toll on her appearance. She has found happiness in a new marriage, and she wants to feel confident when they are in public together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Frizzy to Fine
programme.desc: Zina is a makeup artist by trade – a woman who encourages people to look their best to show off their spirit. However, spending all her time working and taking care of her children, Zina realizes she doesn't live by her own advice.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Emma Singh
programme.desc: Busy mum and part time student Emma Singh has a taste for the bad things in life and it shows big time on her face. Cosmetic surgeon Jan Stanek plans to get Emma to travel more lightly and youthfully by ridding Emma of her excess baggage on day one.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Mr. Right
programme.desc: Ellen is looking for Mr. Right, but due to very busy work and school schedules she hasn't had any time to take care of her looks. We're going make Ellen stand out in the dating competition as we try to make her look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Programming A New Look
programme.desc: Once upon a time, Ian was a groovy party DJ with long hair, spinning disco tunes. Now he's the computer dude with long gray hair. Intense skin treatments, lasik surgery and a Glam overhaul trim 10 years from his looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Hard Hat to Hottie
programme.desc: Laura is a former construction worker who spent years exposed to the harsh elements. Our whole team of experts has kicked into gear to turn back the clock and transform this former construction worker from hard hat to hottie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: I'm No Grandma
programme.desc: Kathy is a mother who has battled health setbacks while raising her kids. She wants to shake off her general malaise and look better as a first step to feeling better. Find out how Kathy goes from dreary to cheery in her journey to look ten years younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Self Conscious To Self Confident
programme.desc: Laura, a public speaker, has lost her self-confidence and is now only self-conscious. Once upbeat and bubbly, she suffered from an illness that took its toll on her appearance and self esteem. Can our experts help Laura regain her identity and a new look?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jilly Graham
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of age-busting experts come to the rescue of Jilly Graham from Bradford.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Soccer Mom to Soccer Bomb!
programme.desc: Colleen Radcliffe is a mother of four and says she doesn't have a spare second to spend on herself. Colleen feels like the old mom with no end in sight, but we're here to teach her that isn't the case. Time to make Colleen look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Photo-phobic To Photogenic
programme.desc: After a rough divorce, Alison has became a single mom. The stress of being the sole breadwinner has left its mark. Will the experts be able to give Alison back her youthful glow?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Spinning a More Youthful Look
programme.desc: Evan is a mobile DJ who is trying to take his business to the next level. Evan hasn't had the time or money to take care his looks but he knows it's absolutely necessary now if his business is going to continue growing.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Meerly Evan
programme.desc: Evan lets the mischievous meerkats loose in Rosie's room to cause havoc. Rosie is devastated when they destroy an irreplaceable photograph of her mother and rages at Evan. She decides once and for all to go back to Bristol.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Evan Meets Elli
programme.desc: Rogue young male elephants are rampaging through Leopard's Den and destroying everything the family have built, so Danny introduces a matriarch elephant in the hope that she will calm them down.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The Westpac chopper crew attempt to save a Waiheke man who has life-threatening injuries after falling off a ladder and a motocross rider is in a bad way after a 100-foot jump goes badly wrong.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The helicopter rescue crew responds to Pauanui to save a truck driver who's smashed through the windscreen after rolling his truck and a Port Charles family is distraught after a young girl is run over by a quad bike.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: A motocross rider may have broken his back after hitting a tree head on at high speed, at a sawmill a man faces its worse nightmares; and a woman is fighting for her life after taking an accidental overdose of her husband's medication.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 18
programme.desc: The roaring sounds of engines and exhausts usually dominate the Nürburgring but on today's episode, we're focusing on something a little quieter. Ever fancied a 15-mile bike ride around the ring, or perhaps a 16-mile run?

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 19
programme.desc: On today's episode, we are going old-timer crazy, like the Mercedes S for example with 160 horsepower that lead Rudolf Caracciola to victory in the 1927 opening race. Do not to miss this old-timer grand prix event!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 20
programme.desc: Phoenix Racing, the successful team from the Eifel Region rocks the DTM. We will be showing you some pit stop training with the Swiss rookie Rahel Frey, a Ford GT kit car and a tuned Honda with a Spaniard at the wheel!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 21
programme.desc: Today on the Nürburgring: Patrick is tearing up the track in an Aston Martin Zagato with 12 cylinders of pure sound! Also on the show: a hummer, a Bremer Clio and a Frenchman in a Ferrari!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 22
programme.desc: Patrick makes André sweat! Also on the show: tourists from all over the world have made their way down to the Green Hell including many Germans, Austrians and five crazy Englishmen in a taxi!

programme.title: Tuning: Alpina / Mercedes
programme.desc: Tuning has to be conspicuous - not for Alpina.The B6 is the best example that Alpina has a penchant for understatement. We tested whether there is more to the Alpina B6 than meets the eye.

programme.title: Tuning: BMW / Chevrolet / Audi
programme.desc: The Kelleners Sport 640i is based on one of the most beautifully designed current 4-door coupés. The tuning forge of racing driver Ralf Kelleners specialises in the conversion of BMWs.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.

programme.title: 4x4: Wildly through the desert
programme.desc: In 2010, BMW and the German racing team X-Raid decided to transform a Mini Countryman into an offroad-vehicle and participate in the world-famous Dakar Rally. Also: the Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, a most exclusive, over-the-top 6-wheel off-road monster...

programme.title: 4x4: Trendy City - SUVs
programme.desc: City-SUVs are the latest trend in the automotive world. They aren't necessarily made for offroad terrain but attract customers through their modern and urban design. In this episode, the Subaru XV shows its offroad skills, and the Nissan Juke is take…

programme.title: 4x4: Land Rover Special
programme.desc: The Land Rover Defender is one of the oldest offroad car models. It may be loud and uncomfortable, but it's absolutely authentic in its simplicity. We took a look at this iconic vehicle and 70 years of Land Rover history.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.desc: A shuttle crashes on a beach after being pursued by a second Taelon piloted shuttle. When Liam locates the survivor (a Taelon called Belleye), he claims to want to help the Resistance take back Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Vanished
